text: The Cirocha is a river in the Prešov Region in eastern Slovakia and is a right tributary of the river Laborec. The Cirocha is long. Its drainage basin has an area of . The river starts in the Bukovec Mountains, near the border between Poland and Slovakia. It flows southwest after a few kilometres into the Starina reservoir. It then flows through the municipalities of Snina and Stakčín. Its mouth is at the Laborec river near Humenné. Category:Rivers of Slovakia
title: Cirocha
